body: - Update `codespan-reporting` dependency to 0.13 (#1662, #1661)

- Improve lifetime-related diagnostics (#1651, #1654)
- Consolidate associated functions into fewer impl blocks to improve rustdoc (#1652, #1655)
- Support `std::vector` of non-move-constructible element type (#1646)
- Simplify implementation of Vec\<String\> (#1640, thanks @anforowicz)

- Fix _"expected a FnOnce() closure"_ build error on unsafe Rust fn with no args (#1637)
- Add derive(BitAnd, BitOr, BitXor) for enums (#1639)

- Fix compiler warning when passing a rust::Fn with a generic return type such as Vec\<T\> from Rust to C++ (#1633)
- Suppress warnings in generated code under GCC's missing-declarations setting (#1635)
- Fix MSVC warning on large negative enum discriminant values (#1636)
- Fix _"cannot find attribute 'serde' in this scope"_ build error using Serde derives with #\[serde(…)\] on a shared struct (#1627)
- Fix _"Unable to resolve type 'str'"_ build error in C++ signatures containing &'static str in return type (#1623)
- Better support extern function signatures containing elided lifetimes (#1621)

- Fix macro redefinition warning when using `-DRUST_CXX_NO_EXCEPTIONS` in some compilers (#1616)
- Support `#[derive(Default)]` on enums (#1618)
- Support non-`repr(C)` Rust types that have methods implemented by C++ (#1620)

- Allow unpinned mutable reference for any Unpin type (#1610)
- Support slice of type alias of Rust types (#1613)

- Allow extern types to appear in Box and Vec (#1605)
- Fix elided\_lifetimes\_in\_paths warning on type aliases that have lifetimes (#1608)
- More precise handling of #\[cfg(…)\] attributes (#1598, #1599, #1604)
- Disable -Wshadow-field-in-constructor and -Wdollar-in-identifier-extension in generated code (#1591, #1593)

- Improve panic location reported by SharedPtr::from_raw (#1581)
- Support UniquePtr and SharedPtr with array types (#1582)
- Support shared ptr with not destructible T (#1579)
- Support older releases of Bazel Rust rules (#1577, thanks @spectraldoy)
- Update `foldhash` dependency to 0.2
- Add `CxxVector::capacity` and `CxxVector::reserve` (#1300, #1572, thanks @russelltg)

- Improve `SharedPtr` documentation (#1569)
- Add `SharedPtr::from_raw` and `impl From<UniquePtr<T>> for SharedPtr<T>` (#1005, #1568)
- Add `SharedPtr::pin_mut_unchecked`, `SharedPtr::as_ptr`, `SharedPtr::as_mut_ptr` (#1570)
- Support #\[repr(align(…))\] attribute on shared structs (#902, #1567, thanks @mxxo)
- Recognize when exceptions are disabled (#1174, #1557, #1558)

- Support associated functions and static member functions (#1546, #1547, #1548)
- Improve type and method naming collision error messages (#1543, #1544)
- Strengthen static assertion generated with `unique_ptr<T>` bindings (#1536, thanks @anforowicz)
- Set build.rs to rerun on changes to file containing bridge module (#1462, thanks @nyurik)
- Delete #\[automatically_derived\] on impl blocks that are not trait impls (#1537)
- Recognize `extern "Rust" fn main()` as a special case that translates to `int main` (#1531)
- Add `extern "C++-unwind"` (#1529, thanks @Berrysoft)
- Work around clippy reporting borrow_as_ptr lint inside generated code (#1510)
